\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.1}{\ignorespaces Raw data and fits for normal mode decomposition in (a) time-, and (b) frequency-domain analysis for two of the [100] phonon modes from the conventional unit cell for $N_0=10$ [see Fig. \ref {F-dispersion}(b)] The inset in (a) shows the convergence of the lifetime according to Eq. \textup {\hbox {\mathsurround \z@ \normalfont (\ignorespaces \ref {E:tau_E_xcorr}\unskip \@@italiccorr )}}. In (b), the vertical lines denote the frequency predicted from harmonic lattice dynamics calculations.}}{22}{figure.2.1}
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.2}{\ignorespaces The phonon spectral energy density ($\Phi $) is plotted as larger blue circles. The proposed alternative expression for the phonon spectral energy density ($\Phi '$) is plotted as smaller green points. The wavevector is ($\pi /2a$,0,0). Note that peak broadening at higher temperatures and frequencies above $10$ rads/ps can force peaks close in frequency for $\Phi '$ to be fit as a single Lorentzian function. $\Phi $ does not suffer from this issue since the broadened peaks can be fit individually.}}{27}{figure.2.2}
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.3}{\ignorespaces Comparison of the phonon frequencies and lifetimes predicted using $\Phi $ ($\omega $ and $\tau $) and $\Phi '$ ($\omega ^{'}$ and $\tau ^{'}$) for LJ argon at temperatures of (a) 5 K, (b) 20 K, and (c) 40 K. The phonon frequencies agree well at all three temperatures, while the phonon lifetimes show large scatter.}}{29}{figure.2.3}
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.4}{\ignorespaces Comparison of the phonon frequencies and lifetimes predicted using $\Phi $ ($\omega $ and $\tau $) and $\Phi '$ ($\omega '$ and $\tau '$) for SW silicon. The phonon frequencies agree well, while the phonon lifetimes show large scatter.}}{33}{figure.2.4}
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.5}{\ignorespaces Comparison of the phonon frequencies and lifetimes predicted using $\Phi $ ($\omega ,\tau $) and $\Phi '$ ($\omega ',\tau '$) for a (8,8) CNT modeled using the REBO potential. The phonon frequencies agree well, while the phonon lifetimes show large scatter.}}{35}{figure.2.5}
